posts.name: philso
posts.cooked:
Are there any 90 degree brackets available that look like this for joining a 2" x 1" tube to a flat plate or another 2" x 1" tube? As drawn, it is 2" x 4" x 2". It’s okay if it ends up being 2" x 2" x 2".

I was not able to find anything like it at Thriftybot, WCP , AndyMark, or VEXPro. The following are the only ones I found but they are either not the right size, are not pre-drilled , and/or have a gap where we would want to have a fold in the material. We also found some very small brackets with only one hole on each side.

The Bumper Wood Corner Bracket is designed to connect two plywood planks together to form a strong 90 degree bumper corner.

The Left Triangle Bracket was originally designed for the AM14U2, AM14U3 and AM14U4 chassis as a robust backing for mounting bumpers. It's also perfect for making robust 90 degree connections between two robot frame sections.

Sorry. I had a screenshot from the CAD all ready to include in my post but forgot to include it. Unfortunately, it looks like the students have now totally deleted the part from even the part studio. They have since replaced it with a part from WCP .

42.82 KB

The original part was similar to this one from AndyMark but measured 2" along the bend and was 2" along one leg and 4" along the other leg, with holes in a 1/2" grid. My gut feeling is that a single piece bracket would make the joint much more rigid than using two small brackets for our applications.
